11#ifndef MODULES_RTP_RTCP_INCLUDE_RTP_HEADER_EXTENSION_MAP_H_
12#define MODULES_RTP_RTCP_INCLUDE_RTP_HEADER_EXTENSION_MAP_H_
13
14#include <stdint.h>
15
16#include <string>
17
18#include "api/array_view.h"
19#include "api/rtp_parameters.h"
20#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_rtcp_defines.h"
21#include "rtc_base/checks.h"
22
23namespace webrtc {
24
25class RtpHeaderExtensionMap {
26 public:
27 static constexpr RTPExtensionType kInvalidType = kRtpExtensionNone;
28 static constexpr int kInvalidId = 0;
29
30 RtpHeaderExtensionMap();
31 explicit RtpHeaderExtensionMap(bool extmap_allow_mixed);
32 explicit RtpHeaderExtensionMap(rtc::ArrayView<const RtpExtension> extensions);
33
34 template <typename Extension>
35 bool Register(int id) {
36 return Register(id, Extension::kId, Extension::kUri);
37 }
38 bool RegisterByType(int id, RTPExtensionType type);
39 bool RegisterByUri(int id, absl::string_view uri);
40
41 bool IsRegistered(RTPExtensionType type) const {
42 return GetId(type) != kInvalidId;
43 }
44 // Return kInvalidType if not found.
45 RTPExtensionType GetType(int id) const;
46 // Return kInvalidId if not found.
47 uint8_t GetId(RTPExtensionType type) const {
48 RTC_DCHECK_GT(type, kRtpExtensionNone);
49 RTC_DCHECK_LT(type, kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions);
50 return ids_[type];
51 }
52
53 int32_t Deregister(RTPExtensionType type);
54 void Deregister(absl::string_view uri);
55
56 // Corresponds to the SDP attribute extmap-allow-mixed, see RFC8285.
57 // Set to true if it's allowed to mix one- and two-byte RTP header extensions
58 // in the same stream.
59 bool ExtmapAllowMixed() const { return extmap_allow_mixed_; }
60 void SetExtmapAllowMixed(bool extmap_allow_mixed) {
61 extmap_allow_mixed_ = extmap_allow_mixed;
62 }
63
64 private:
65 bool Register(int id, RTPExtensionType type, const char* uri);
66
67 uint8_t ids_[kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions];
68 bool extmap_allow_mixed_;
69};
70
71} // namespace webrtc
72
73#endif // MODULES_RTP_RTCP_INCLUDE_RTP_HEADER_EXTENSION_MAP_H_
